

BASIC
 <Ctrl+a c> open bash on region

REGIONS
 <Ctrl+a S> split horizontally
 <Ctrl+a |> split vertically
 <Ctrl+a X> remove active region
 <Ctrl+a number[0-9]> change to screen num
 <Ctrl+a Q> active region is the only seen
 <Ctrl+a :resize +10> increase 10 lines horizontally

DEATACH
 <Ctrl+a d> deatach

COPY TO CLIPBOARD
 1. <Ctrl+a> [ -> enter copy mode
 2. space -> start selecting
 3. space -> copy selected text
 in a terminal inside screen:
   4. cat | xsel -b 
   5. <Ctrl+a> ] -> bulk screen buffer 
   6. <Ctrl+d> -> send EOF 
